== Sketcher Workbench == <!--T:40-->

{| cellpadding=5
| placeholder for image/gif
| Create defining external geometry: It is now possible to create 'real' external geometry in Sketcher and toggle between defining and construction mode.
[https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17736 Pull request #17736]
|}

{| cellpadding=5
| placeholder for image/gif
| Create intersection external geometry: It is now possible to create external geometry in Sketcher which is based on the selected reference geometry and the intersection of the sketch plane. The default mode is the current one: create a projection of the external feature onto the sketch plane.
[https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17736 Pull request #17736]
|}

{| cellpadding=5
| placeholder for image/gif
| Create external geometry from face selection: It is now possible to create external geometry (both projection and intersection) in Sketcher by selecting a face.
[https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17736 Pull request #17736]
|}

=== Further Sketcher improvements === <!--T:41-->

<!--T:53-->
* It is now possible to directly use external geometry as input for tools like offset or transform (array), for both external construction and defining geometry [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17615 Pull request #17615]
* The Sketcher axes are now displayed with infinite length. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17312 Pull request #17312]

